01:28.846 --> 01:30.813
I feel I've outgrown walgreens.

01:30.848 --> 01:33.816
Someday, I'd like to make it
to the big city

01:33.851 --> 01:36.285
and go to a Duane Reade.

01:36.321 --> 01:38.955
Oh, you have not <i> lived</i> until
you've been to Duane Reade.

01:38.990 --> 01:41.424
Duane Reade is magical!

01:41.459 --> 01:44.827
Oh! They have these <i> divine</i>
mini nail clippers!

01:44.862 --> 01:46.829
I need to hear this.

01:46.864 --> 01:48.831
There's a woman out front
getting signatures

01:48.866 --> 01:51.400
where last week,
I was totally ignored.

01:53.338 --> 01:55.705
Hey, look, it's DJ Iron Monkey!

01:55.740 --> 01:56.872
Ooh, I love him!

01:56.908 --> 01:58.641
Oh, my God!
Look at his yacht!

01:58.676 --> 02:01.577
He's not only rich,
he's incredibly wealthy, too.

02:01.613 --> 02:03.312
But he's also
an environmentalist.

02:03.348 --> 02:04.847
His yacht
is solar-powered.

02:04.882 --> 02:07.350
Forget the sun.
What's powering those abs?

02:07.385 --> 02:09.752
Look at the definition
on those abs!

02:09.787 --> 02:12.755
Yep. Abs.

02:12.790 --> 02:15.825
Listen to what he says
about his charity work.

02:15.860 --> 02:18.961
"DJ Iron Monkey doesn't do it
to get his name out there.

02:18.997 --> 02:20.830
"DJ Iron Monkey does it

02:20.865 --> 02:23.966
"because DJ Iron Monkey thinks
it's amazing,

02:24.002 --> 02:26.535
like DJ Iron Monkey's
music."

02:26.571 --> 02:29.338
[ Sighs ]
These are his own words.

02:29.374 --> 02:31.007
You know, I've never used
these ribbed ones,

02:31.042 --> 02:33.809
but I assume
they work like gangbusters.

02:37.135 --> 02:40.770
Ah, home is where the...
fliers are?!

02:44.776 --> 02:47.444
Ugh! There's got to be
a better way.

02:52.217 --> 02:54.784
Whoa! I thought
you were gonna be David Blaine!

02:54.820 --> 02:56.319
These damn fliers!

02:56.355 --> 02:58.054
I'm telling you,
they're a fire hazard.

02:58.090 --> 02:59.789
I'm sick of 'em!
Makes me want to move.

02:59.825 --> 03:01.057
I mean who needs --

03:01.093 --> 03:04.060
"Hillside Acres,
a gated community.

03:04.096 --> 03:06.062
Tired of all those fliers
on your door?"

03:06.098 --> 03:07.931
Oh, my God!
I was just saying that!

03:07.966 --> 03:10.200
Then we wouldn't have to put up
with this trash anymore.

03:10.235 --> 03:13.670
10% off my next treat at TCBY?!

03:13.705 --> 03:16.873
Wait a minute.
Are these <i> all</i> amazing?

03:21.046 --> 03:22.746
"Missing child."

03:22.781 --> 03:24.748
I don't see how that's a deal.

03:24.783 --> 03:27.083
[ Mariachi music plays ]

03:27.119 --> 03:28.852
What am I doing wrong?

03:28.887 --> 03:31.221
That blonde outside of walgreens
was getting signatures.

03:31.256 --> 03:32.789
Come on, Hayley.

03:32.824 --> 03:34.357
Everyone knows
blondes get more attention.

03:34.393 --> 03:36.092
Scientists have proven it.

03:36.128 --> 03:37.794
But their research was ignored

03:37.829 --> 03:40.096
because they were boring,
brown-haired scientists.

03:40.132 --> 03:44.367
From the gentlemen at the bar.

03:44.403 --> 03:47.303
Looks like brunettes
get attention, too.

03:48.874 --> 03:51.975
That's not yours!
That is <i> not</i> for you!

03:52.010 --> 03:55.011
Come on! Be serious!
It's for the blonde!

03:56.815 --> 03:58.148
Thanks!

03:58.183 --> 04:00.450
Uh, she'll be fine.
Don't worry about her.

04:00.485 --> 04:02.218
We're not!

04:04.456 --> 04:07.157
Rosalie's Pizza? I have
a very important question.

04:07.192 --> 04:09.159
Do you deliver
to Hillside Acres?

04:09.194 --> 04:10.493
Yes! Good, good.

04:10.529 --> 04:12.962
My next question,
which is so important

04:12.998 --> 04:14.831
that it should have been
my first and only question --

04:14.866 --> 04:17.233
do you accept
half-burnt coupons?

04:17.269 --> 04:19.235
He's checking.
He's checking!

04:19.271 --> 04:21.404
Whoo-hoo! Maybe!

04:23.041 --> 04:24.741
Dad, these houses
aren't done yet.

04:24.776 --> 04:26.142
Besides, the gate's locked.

04:26.178 --> 04:28.011
That <i> is</i> a beautiful gate!

04:28.046 --> 04:30.413
And imagine how many fliers
this thing can hold!

04:30.449 --> 04:33.149
Wait, I thought we're moving
to get <i> away</i> from the fliers?

04:33.185 --> 04:34.751
Oh, lord, no.
Keep up, Steve.

04:34.786 --> 04:36.853
We're moving here
to keep the riffraff out.

04:36.888 --> 04:39.122
The fact that we'll be tripling
our flier intake

04:39.157 --> 04:42.992
is just a huge,
huge, huge,<i> huge...</i>

04:43.028 --> 04:44.494
What were we talking about?

04:44.529 --> 04:46.496
About why on earth we would
leave our perfectly good house

04:46.531 --> 04:48.965
where our family has
so many memories to come here.

04:49.000 --> 04:50.366
It's the goddamn riffraff!

04:50.402 --> 04:52.168
But this gate will
keep them out!

04:52.204 --> 04:53.937
I mean, were they
to try to get in,

04:53.972 --> 04:56.172
they would have to kneel down,
raise their partner's foot,

04:56.208 --> 04:57.941
and hoist them over...

04:59.211 --> 05:00.777
Aah! Oof!

05:00.812 --> 05:03.079
And who's to say
how his accomplice would get in?

05:03.115 --> 05:07.183
[ Dogs barking ]

05:07.219 --> 05:08.551
Oh, look!

05:08.587 --> 05:10.920
A private mini zoo
just for the residents.

05:10.956 --> 05:12.455
Dad, those are guard dogs.

05:12.491 --> 05:14.190
Well, they should all be fired,

05:14.226 --> 05:16.893
'cause we got in here
pretty easily, especially me.

05:16.928 --> 05:20.363
Steve, there's our dream house.

05:20.398 --> 05:22.132
Where?

05:22.167 --> 05:24.100
You see the one that's bathed
in that ray of sunlight?

05:24.136 --> 05:26.236
[ Harp strums ]

05:26.271 --> 05:29.305
It's the one right next to it.

05:29.341 --> 05:32.475
Yeah, that's the one.

05:35.113 --> 05:37.814
[ Scatting ]

05:37.849 --> 05:39.482
♪ I'm gonna go
hear some jazz at Pips ♪

05:39.518 --> 05:41.818
♪ and see some
gorgeous half-black girls ♪

05:41.853 --> 05:43.353
You want to go, Francine?

05:43.388 --> 05:45.355
Roger, did we bring
all the bags in?

05:45.390 --> 05:46.956
I can't find my hair dye.

05:46.992 --> 05:48.558
Francine?!

05:48.593 --> 05:51.127
But if you're there, then
I must have been talking to...

05:51.163 --> 05:53.963
[ Gasps ]
...Dolly Parton?!

05:53.999 --> 05:55.365
Oh, my God!

05:55.400 --> 05:57.534
Dolly, it's such an honor
to have you in our house!

05:57.569 --> 05:59.135
I've seen
"Smoky Mountain Christmas"

05:59.171 --> 06:00.136
like 400 times!

06:00.172 --> 06:01.237
Turn, Dolly!

06:01.273 --> 06:02.539
Spin and point your face at me

06:02.574 --> 06:04.274
as soon as you feel comfortable!

06:06.411 --> 06:09.479
"Nine to five," alive!
It's Hayley!

06:12.383 --> 06:14.216
<i>This</i> I can work with.

06:14.251 --> 06:16.485
I hope you're
up for some fun, blondie.

06:16.520 --> 06:19.621
Thanks, but I didn't dye my hair
to have fun, okay?

06:19.657 --> 06:21.223
I did it so that people
would pay more attention

06:21.258 --> 06:22.424
to what I have to say.

06:22.460 --> 06:24.159
Oh, yeah, of course.
That's what I meant.

06:24.195 --> 06:26.428
And I know where you can make
the most difference --

06:26.464 --> 06:28.397
celebrity charity events.

06:28.432 --> 06:30.099
Roger, come on.

06:30.134 --> 06:31.500
I always thought those events
were just publicity stunts.

06:31.535 --> 06:33.135
Oh, no way.

06:33.170 --> 06:35.004
The bigger the dollars,
the bigger the change.

06:35.039 --> 06:38.974
That's why tonight, we're
going to a benefit at Dush.

06:39.010 --> 06:40.976
[ Sighs ] I don't know.

06:41.012 --> 06:42.978
I even have the perfect guide.

06:43.014 --> 06:44.646
Jojo Quinoa!

06:44.682 --> 06:48.517
And just like the Superfood,
I'm for sale at Trader Joe's.

06:48.552 --> 06:50.986
Behind Trader Joe's.

06:51.022 --> 06:52.354
For free.

06:55.026 --> 06:58.160
We can put a pool table
over here.

06:58.195 --> 07:01.430
Oh, and this is a perfect spot
for a breakfast nook.

07:01.465 --> 07:04.566
Steve, come pretend
we're having cereal!

07:04.602 --> 07:06.301
Is something wrong, son?

07:06.337 --> 07:08.203
No, dad, nothing's wrong.

07:10.374 --> 07:13.609
It's clear you're
not feeling the house, Steve.

07:13.644 --> 07:15.477
Well, what do
you want me to do, huh?

07:15.513 --> 07:17.246
Pretend I like it

07:17.281 --> 07:19.281
when I really don't want to
move in the first place?!

07:19.316 --> 07:21.683
[ Grunts ]
Pssh!

07:21.719 --> 07:23.419
Damn it, son!
Don't you get it?!

07:23.454 --> 07:27.089
Change is good!
Come on! Follow me!

07:27.124 --> 07:30.492
Son, this is <i> your</i> room.

07:30.528 --> 07:32.227
Go on -- take a look
out that door there.

07:32.263 --> 07:33.562
Tell me what you see.

07:33.597 --> 07:36.532
It's a sun deck.

07:36.567 --> 07:38.100
A-and there's a jacuzzi!

07:38.135 --> 07:40.636
Just imagine
all the killer parties

07:40.671 --> 07:42.237
you're gonna have up here.

07:42.273 --> 07:43.772
This is the house, Steve.

07:43.808 --> 07:46.775
This is where your life
finally comes together.

07:46.811 --> 07:48.777
My life's okay.
It sucks.

07:48.813 --> 07:50.512
But think about
what it <i> could</i> be.

07:50.548 --> 07:52.448
[ Funky music playing ]

07:54.000 --> 08:00.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

08:01.125 --> 08:02.691
I like video games.

08:05.129 --> 08:07.496
I like Scaredy Boys.

08:09.800 --> 08:14.503
Uh...you and I clearly
have stuff we need to work out.

08:19.610 --> 08:23.112
I'm beginning
to get the picture, papa.

08:23.147 --> 08:25.514
[ Techno music plays ]

08:28.652 --> 08:30.752
This party is amazing.

08:30.788 --> 08:33.222
There must be so much money
being raised.

08:33.256 --> 08:36.625
Cocaine is so much more fun
when it's for a good cause.

08:36.659 --> 08:38.360
Hey, speaking of causes,

08:38.395 --> 08:40.229
have you ever heard of
garbage island?

08:40.264 --> 08:42.364
I can't wait
to hear all about it.

08:42.399 --> 08:43.698
Let me go grab us
a couple of drinks

08:43.734 --> 08:45.167
so we don't get dry mouth

08:45.202 --> 08:48.170
when we talk about garbage
for hours.

08:48.205 --> 08:50.706
I think
they're serving owl here.

08:50.741 --> 08:52.708
Or maybe that was a display.

08:52.743 --> 08:54.309
Either way, I ate an owl.

08:54.345 --> 08:56.345
Sounds like we're both
knockin' it out of the park!

08:56.347 --> 08:57.846
Man, this blonde hair
is working.

08:57.882 --> 09:00.315
Everybody's listening to me
about garbage island.

09:00.351 --> 09:01.850
I told you!

09:01.886 --> 09:04.319
Hayley, I just found out

09:04.355 --> 09:07.723
about a charity gala
poppin' off in Vegas!

09:07.758 --> 09:09.258
I guess it's for

09:09.293 --> 09:11.426
one of the hottest
new causes out there.

09:11.462 --> 09:12.828
How are we gonna get to Vegas?

09:12.863 --> 09:15.664
Easy!
We'll take my private jet!

09:15.699 --> 09:17.199
Private jet?

09:17.234 --> 09:19.334
I-isn't that the most wasteful
way to travel?

09:19.370 --> 09:21.537
Got to burn money
to raise money!

09:21.572 --> 09:23.839
Hayley, the earth is dying.

09:23.874 --> 09:25.674
We don't have time
to ride a bus.

09:25.709 --> 09:26.775
Well...
[ Scoffs ]

09:26.810 --> 09:28.410
I guess it's for a good cause.

09:28.445 --> 09:29.444
Let's do it.

09:29.480 --> 09:30.712
[ Coughs ]

09:30.748 --> 09:32.314
You want to know what's crazy?

09:32.349 --> 09:35.284
This is <i> not</i> the owl
I ate earlier.

09:35.319 --> 09:36.685
[ Insects chirping ]

09:36.720 --> 09:38.554
See, Steve,
when you live on a hill,

09:38.589 --> 09:40.289
you can look down on everyone.

09:40.324 --> 09:42.157
It's not the only reason
to live on a hill,

09:42.193 --> 09:43.425
but it's the main one.

09:43.460 --> 09:45.494
Yeah, I'm starting
to warm up to the idea

09:45.529 --> 09:47.229
of living in a gated community.

09:47.264 --> 09:49.231
Mind if I turn on the jets?

09:49.266 --> 09:51.600
Bub-bub-bub-bub-bub-bub, bub-bub-bub-bub-bub-bub,
bub-bub-bub-bub-bub-bub.

09:51.635 --> 09:53.302
[ Vehicle approaching ]

09:53.337 --> 09:57.306
Looks like the security patrol
is doing the rounds.

09:57.341 --> 09:59.641
Terrible for us now,
but great for when we live here.

10:01.378 --> 10:03.345
All right, boys.
You're on your own tonight.

10:03.380 --> 10:05.881
I'm taking an HTML class
at the learning annex.

10:05.916 --> 10:09.618
They say the future
of groundskeeping is all online.

10:09.653 --> 10:11.420
[ All sniffing, whine ]

10:13.757 --> 10:15.624
[ Growling, barking ]

10:18.495 --> 10:19.561
Dad?

10:19.597 --> 10:22.331
Did you close the front door?

10:22.366 --> 10:23.632
Ohh!

10:27.638 --> 10:29.738
I don't think I'm gonna
follow Billy Ocean

10:29.773 --> 10:30.839
on Instagram anymore.

10:30.874 --> 10:32.641
He never leaves the bathroom.

10:32.676 --> 10:36.778
Oh, Hayley and Roger
are tearing it up in Vegas.

10:36.814 --> 10:38.247
What?!
[ Cellphone beeps ]

10:38.282 --> 10:40.382
[ Ringing ]
Hayley, where are you?

10:40.417 --> 10:42.918
I'm at a charity event in Vegas.

10:42.953 --> 10:44.519
It's my fifth one tonight!

10:44.555 --> 10:46.655
We're on a charity crawl!
Whoo!

10:46.690 --> 10:48.523
Honey, I'm worried
you're losing sight of --

10:48.559 --> 10:49.958
I got to go.

10:49.994 --> 10:51.727
Someone's about to donate
all over my stomach.

10:51.762 --> 10:53.962
[ Cellphone beeps ]

10:55.933 --> 10:58.767
Whoa. You're, like,
super-hot at charity.

10:58.802 --> 11:00.469
Thank you.

11:00.504 --> 11:02.771
You need to come with me
to DJ Iron Monkey's yacht

11:02.806 --> 11:05.240
for the biggest charity event
of the decade.

11:05.276 --> 11:07.909
So, we're not counting
the Jerry Lewis Telethon in 2008

11:07.945 --> 11:10.512
when Richard Chamberlain just
showed up to sing three songs

11:10.547 --> 11:12.514
and half the audience
had heart attacks?

11:12.549 --> 11:14.383
Actually, Richard Chamberlain
will be there.

11:14.418 --> 11:17.819
[ Screams ]

11:24.328 --> 11:27.696
As you'll see, this whole yacht
runs on solar power.

11:27.731 --> 11:30.332
Dude, that shit's tight.
I know.

11:30.367 --> 11:33.468
Also, if you're wondering
why all the ladies are topless,

11:33.504 --> 11:36.571
we banned all clothes
made in Chinese sweatshops.

11:36.607 --> 11:40.442
Well, if them's the rules.

11:40.477 --> 11:43.812
These were made in Canada,
but don't tell anybody.

11:43.847 --> 11:46.815
So, did you find any chicks
for the party?

11:46.850 --> 11:48.950
Yeah, some blonde from Virginia.

11:48.986 --> 11:50.686
She's buying into
all that charity crap.

11:50.721 --> 11:51.953
So if you want to get with her,

11:51.989 --> 11:53.822
just ask her about her causes.

11:53.857 --> 11:56.558
Cool. Thanks again
for doing this, man.

11:56.593 --> 11:58.560
This probably isn't
what you went to college for,

11:58.595 --> 12:00.429
so I really appreciate it.

12:00.464 --> 12:01.930
No, no.
It's cool. It's cool.

12:01.965 --> 12:04.299
I majored in art history,
but part of going to college

12:04.335 --> 12:06.601
is figuring out
what you <i> don't</i> want to do.

12:08.351 --> 12:09.231
[ Techno music plays ]

12:11.354 --> 12:12.754
<i>Charity.</i>

12:12.789 --> 12:14.322
[ Cheers and applause ]

12:14.357 --> 12:16.304
This feels amazing!

12:16.574 --> 12:18.407
We should raise money
for ecstasy!

12:18.442 --> 12:20.409
We're saving the world, girl!

12:20.444 --> 12:22.278
I just wish we had gum!

12:22.313 --> 12:25.281
Do you have any gum?
Gum? I'd love some gum!

12:25.316 --> 12:27.449
Let's talk about this forever!

12:34.759 --> 12:38.727
I can't believe
I'm in Iron Monkey's head.

12:38.763 --> 12:40.996
Iron Monkey can't believe
you are, either.

12:41.032 --> 12:44.733
Iron Monkey can't
believe a lot of things.

12:44.769 --> 12:47.603
It's so great that
you're doing this for charity.

12:47.638 --> 12:49.872
Uh, but what's the cause
we're raising money for again?

12:49.907 --> 12:51.640
The environment.

12:51.676 --> 12:54.643
No one even realizes how
important the environment is.

12:54.679 --> 12:56.645
I mean, where would we be
without it?

12:56.681 --> 12:59.048
Space? No, thanks.

12:59.083 --> 13:01.517
I'm too scared of black holes
to live there.

13:01.552 --> 13:05.054
Oh, me too.
Me too, Iron Monkey.

13:05.089 --> 13:07.089
How about I show you
around the ship,

13:07.124 --> 13:09.525
so you can see all the ways
this mega yacht

13:09.560 --> 13:12.094
protects this...
environment?

13:19.470 --> 13:20.970
<i>Charity.</i>

13:21.005 --> 13:23.372
[ Dogs barking ]

13:23.407 --> 13:25.374
Dad, these dogs are relentless!

13:25.409 --> 13:26.876
When are they gonna give up?!

13:26.911 --> 13:29.345
Hang in there, son.
Those losers aren't getting in.

13:29.380 --> 13:31.347
Yeah, I called you losers!

13:31.382 --> 13:32.581
[ Barking stops ]

13:32.617 --> 13:34.917
Do...do you think
they went away?

13:34.952 --> 13:36.652
Yeah.
I called them losers.

13:36.687 --> 13:37.920
You don't come back from that.

13:37.955 --> 13:39.388
[ Scraping ]

13:39.423 --> 13:40.956
They're on the roof!

13:40.992 --> 13:43.792
Steve, you didn't by any chance
secure the fireplace, did --

13:43.828 --> 13:45.527
[ Both gasp ]
[ Growling ]

13:45.563 --> 13:46.762
[ Dog whines, barks ]

13:46.797 --> 13:48.364
[ Dog whines ]

13:48.399 --> 13:51.500
I don't think this bit
gets any funnier, Steve! Run!

13:54.538 --> 13:56.505
[ Dogs barking ]
Aah!

13:56.540 --> 13:58.774
[ Dog whimpering ]

13:58.809 --> 14:00.042
To the sun deck!

14:08.686 --> 14:11.921
Oh, my God!
Dad, are you okay?!

14:13.090 --> 14:14.924
I'm sorry, Steve.
You've been in my study.

14:14.959 --> 14:16.926
Have you seen a medical-school
degree on the wall?

14:16.961 --> 14:18.394
I don't know!

14:18.429 --> 14:19.795
Sorry for being condescending.

14:19.830 --> 14:21.697
Maybe it's
the first sign of rabies.

14:21.732 --> 14:24.800
But then again, I'm not
a doctor, so I don't know!

14:24.835 --> 14:26.802
Sorry. That's
the rabies talking.

14:26.837 --> 14:27.937
Maybe.

14:27.972 --> 14:29.905
[ Techno music plays ]

14:32.777 --> 14:34.009
Do you like the table?

14:34.045 --> 14:37.146
It's one solid,
800-pound piece of cork.

14:37.181 --> 14:38.881
The ship builder
<i>really</i> didn't want me

14:38.916 --> 14:40.616
to put this in the hull.

14:40.651 --> 14:42.618
But that just
made me want it more.

14:42.653 --> 14:44.153
Aren't cork trees endangered?

14:44.188 --> 14:46.822
That's why it's so important
to cut them down now.

14:46.857 --> 14:48.090
Does that make sense?

14:48.125 --> 14:50.092
Shh.
Drink your wine.

14:50.127 --> 14:51.427
[ Cellphone rings ]

14:51.462 --> 14:52.695
Yello?

14:52.730 --> 14:54.630
Yo, Monkey,
I got another girl lined up.

14:54.665 --> 14:56.098
She's into threesomes,

14:56.133 --> 14:58.901
but I <i> may</i> get her
to agree to a twosome.

14:58.936 --> 15:00.936
I got to take this.

15:08.179 --> 15:10.879
Oh, my God! Whales!

15:10.915 --> 15:13.615
Oh, my God...slave whales!

15:13.651 --> 15:15.918
[ Whale sings ]

15:17.955 --> 15:21.790
This yacht's not solar-powered.
It's -- it's whale-powered!

15:21.826 --> 15:24.793
Iron Monkey's a phony!
What a fake!

15:24.829 --> 15:27.062
He's not changing anything.
He's just partying.

15:27.098 --> 15:28.998
That's all anyone's doing here.

15:30.067 --> 15:32.167
Including <i> you.</i>

15:32.203 --> 15:35.504
You dyed your hair
so people would listen to you.

15:35.539 --> 15:37.506
But then
you just got super-drunk,

15:37.541 --> 15:39.908
and you totally forgot
to talk about your stuff.

15:39.944 --> 15:42.511
I came here
to make a difference,

15:42.546 --> 15:44.179
and I am going to make one.

15:44.215 --> 15:47.549
Starting by freeing
those whales.

15:49.787 --> 15:52.755
He threw these out
without cutting them?!

15:52.790 --> 15:55.524
Is there no level
to which he won't stoop?!

15:57.695 --> 15:59.928
Wait. What?
Mom?!

15:59.964 --> 16:01.930
Well, this ain't your daddy.

16:01.966 --> 16:04.933
What are you doing here?
And why are you dressed like me?

16:04.969 --> 16:07.202
I came because I knew
you'd lost your way.

16:07.238 --> 16:09.905
I'm here to remind you
of who you are!

16:09.940 --> 16:11.173
That's really sweet, mom.

16:11.208 --> 16:14.176
But I already figured it out
for myself.

16:14.211 --> 16:15.244
Two minutes ago.

16:15.279 --> 16:16.712
Really?

16:16.747 --> 16:20.049
I made my hair ugly,
took an 11-hour flight,

16:20.084 --> 16:24.653
then paid a Mallorcan fisherman
a thousand Mallorcan money units

16:24.688 --> 16:27.156
to row me out here
all for nothing?!

16:27.191 --> 16:28.757
No, it wasn't.

16:28.793 --> 16:31.126
I need your help
to do something truly good.

16:31.162 --> 16:33.695
[ Dogs barking ]

16:33.731 --> 16:35.931
They're gonna get through!

16:35.966 --> 16:38.934
Just one nail left.

16:38.969 --> 16:40.536
Better make it count.

16:40.571 --> 16:42.104
Goodbye, son.

16:43.641 --> 16:46.008
Dad, wait!
Shoot that propane tank!

16:46.043 --> 16:48.243
Maybe the explosion
will scare off the dogs!

16:48.279 --> 16:50.179
Good thinking!

16:53.250 --> 16:54.883
[ Dogs whimpering ]

16:54.919 --> 16:56.752
You did it!
[ Rumbling ]

16:56.787 --> 16:58.120
Uh-oh, Steve.

16:58.155 --> 17:00.022
It must be connected
to the main gas line.

17:00.057 --> 17:01.690
This whole place is gonna blow!

17:01.725 --> 17:03.692
What are you doing?

17:03.727 --> 17:05.694
Get on.
Now hold on tight.

17:05.729 --> 17:07.162
[ Screams ]

17:07.198 --> 17:08.797
It worked!

17:08.833 --> 17:11.767
Dad, even though we're not
moving into that cool house,

17:11.801 --> 17:13.769
I'll still get to have parties
with girls, right?

17:13.804 --> 17:14.903
Afraid not, Steve.

17:14.939 --> 17:16.872
And we should really talk about

17:16.906 --> 17:19.108
what snot was doing
in your fantasy.

17:19.143 --> 17:20.576
Oh, no!

17:20.611 --> 17:22.211
They're gaining on us!

17:22.246 --> 17:23.878
[ Dogs barking ]

17:23.914 --> 17:25.314
Hang on tight!

17:27.184 --> 17:29.885
[ Grunting ]

17:29.920 --> 17:31.887
[ Both sigh ]

17:31.922 --> 17:35.290
Wait. The mailboxes are
down here by the guard gate?

17:35.326 --> 17:38.026
You have to come all the way
down here to get your mail?

17:38.062 --> 17:40.229
Oh, screw this place.

17:40.264 --> 17:42.865
[ Techno music playing ]

17:42.900 --> 17:45.734
I think the whales
are to the right up here.

17:45.769 --> 17:47.069
Do you mean starboard?

17:47.104 --> 17:49.271
We're on a boat, Hayley.
Start talking boat.

17:49.306 --> 17:50.739
Yeah!

17:50.774 --> 17:51.974
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!

17:52.009 --> 17:53.008
You guys aren't allowed
down here.

17:53.043 --> 17:55.144
Oh...Um...Sorry.

17:55.179 --> 17:57.613
Uh, we were just...

17:57.648 --> 17:59.748
looking for the dance floor.

17:59.783 --> 18:02.251
<i>I'll</i> take you.
It's on the next deck.

18:03.888 --> 18:07.389
No.
I think it's right here.

18:07.424 --> 18:08.924
What?
That's right, lady.

18:08.959 --> 18:11.126
I'm challenging <i> you</i>
to a dance-off.

18:11.162 --> 18:14.730
Unless you don't think
you've got the moves.

18:14.765 --> 18:18.634
Oh, I've got moves
all day till Sunday.

18:18.669 --> 18:20.669
[ Music continues ]

18:24.675 --> 18:26.808
Go free the whales.

18:31.815 --> 18:33.348
We talked about this, Roger.

18:33.384 --> 18:36.051
You're the one who
frees the whales <i> every</i> time.

18:36.086 --> 18:37.920
This was gonna be the time
<i>you</i> did the dance-off,

18:37.955 --> 18:40.289
but here we are,
in the whale room, once again.

18:53.737 --> 18:55.704
[ Muttering ]

18:55.739 --> 18:58.974
[ Whales singing ]

19:02.112 --> 19:04.213
Aww, damn!

19:04.248 --> 19:05.948
Here comes the rebuttal!

19:08.719 --> 19:10.986
<i>You</i> teach people
how to treat you!

19:12.990 --> 19:15.090
[ Music continues ]

19:17.428 --> 19:18.860
[ Both panting ]

19:18.896 --> 19:20.128
That was a'ight.

19:20.164 --> 19:21.863
But let me show you
how it's done.

19:21.899 --> 19:24.266
Make some room.
Make some room!

19:24.301 --> 19:25.367
[ Rumbling ]

19:25.402 --> 19:27.002
[ Both grunt ]
[ Bones crack ]

19:27.037 --> 19:29.004
Whales are free.

19:29.039 --> 19:30.872
It's over. We did it!

19:30.908 --> 19:34.142
All he has to do is get more
whales, and he'll be back at it.

19:34.178 --> 19:36.745
Trust me.
This ocean is lousy with whales.

19:36.780 --> 19:39.748
Now, let's end this
once and for all.

19:39.783 --> 19:42.284
Did you kill this guy?

19:42.319 --> 19:45.287
That's it -- next time,
<i>I'm</i> doing the dance-off!

19:45.322 --> 19:47.289
[ Techno music playing ]

19:47.324 --> 19:49.891
[ All grunting ]

19:49.927 --> 19:51.426
It won't budge!

19:51.462 --> 19:53.095
Let's give up.

19:53.130 --> 19:54.730
We need to find something
to help us pry it out.

19:54.765 --> 19:57.866
Maybe there's something in here.

19:57.901 --> 19:59.268
Tusks.

19:59.303 --> 20:02.004
I think we can no longer
deny the facts.

20:02.039 --> 20:04.406
This guy is an elephant dentist.

20:04.441 --> 20:06.141
[ All grunting ]

20:06.176 --> 20:08.877
[ Creaking ]

20:08.912 --> 20:11.313
[ Pop! ]

20:13.784 --> 20:15.984
[ All scream ]

20:18.522 --> 20:21.490
For the first time in my life,

20:21.525 --> 20:25.193
I feel like I really did
something to help the earth.

20:31.969 --> 20:35.470
Ugh!

20:35.506 --> 20:39.207
Hayley, the oil spill
dyed your hair back to normal.

20:39.243 --> 20:41.416
Everything worked out!

20:47.851 --> 20:50.819
Oh, look.
My cigarettes stayed dry.

20:50.854 --> 20:52.254
[ Lighter clicks ]

